contentrichtext.text: '''Rufinus''' may refer to: *[[Saints Rufinus]], eleven saints named Rufinus in Roman Martyrology *[[Rufinus of Assisi]], 3rd-century saint and martyr *[[Rufinus (French saint)]] (d. 287), Christian martyr *[[Rufinus (Roman governor)]], 3rd century governor of Roman Britain *[[Rufinus (consul)]] (c. 335-395), Eastern Roman statesman *[[Tyrannius Rufinus]] (c. 340-410), Roman monk, historian, and translator *Saint [[Rufinus of Sarsina]] (5th century), bishop of Sarsina *[[Rufinus (poet)]] of the Greek Anthology *[[Rufinus (decretist)]], 12th-century canon lawyer {{hndis}}
